      ],
      "depth": 1,
      "type_signature": "(signal: 1-D numeric array (time-series amplitude values), sampling_rate: positive integer or float (Hz), tol: float (tolerance threshold for peak/segment detection)) -> 1-D integer array of sample indices marking segment boundaries",
      "matched_primitive": null,
      "primitive_binding_confidence": 0.0,
      "primitive_binding_source": "",
      "is_optional": false,
      "is_opaque": false,
      "is_external": false,
      "parallelizable": false,
      "conceptual_summary": "tolerance_gated_periodic_boundary_extractor. Scans a uniformly-sampled scalar time-series to identify quasi-periodic structural boundaries by applying the Gamboa criterion \u2014 a threshold-gated comparison of local amplitude morphology against a tolerance-scaled reference \u2014 partitioning the sequence into contiguous, non-overlapping segments whose edges coincide with detected cycle onsets. The operation maps a continuous 1-D signal into a discrete index set that encodes the topology of its repeating motif structure, collapsing temporal amplitude information into a sparse boundary skeleton. The tolerance parameter acts as a sensitivity knob that trades recall of weak periodicity against false-positive suppression, making the segmentation tunable across signal-to-noise regimes.. Applications: Mechanical vibration analysis: partitioning a rotary machinery accelerometer trace into individual shaft-rotation cycles to isolate per-revolution fault signatures for bearing diagnostics, Astrophysics / pulsar timing: segmenting a radio telescope intensity time-series into individual pulsar emission periods to align and stack pulses for dispersion-measure estimation, Fluid dynamics / rheology: detecting stroke boundaries in oscillatory shear-stress waveforms from a rheometer to extract per-cycle viscoelastic moduli without assuming fixed frequency, Acoustic phonetics: locating glottal closure instants in a laryngograph or microphone waveform to segment voiced speech into individual glottal cycles for pitch-synchronous spectral analysis",
      "critic_notes": "",
      "decomposition_rationale": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": "compute_window_samples",
      "parent_id": "gamboa_segmenter",
      "name": "compute_window_samples",
      "description": "Convert time-based window durations (100ms and 300ms) into integer sample counts based on the sampling rate.",
      "concept_type": "arithmetic",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "name": "sampling_rate",
          "type_desc": "positive float or int (Hz)",
          "constraints": "must be > 0",
          "required": true,
          "default_value_repr": ""
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "v_100ms",
          "type_desc": "positive int (samples)",
          "constraints": "= floor(0.1 * sampling_rate)",
          "required": true,
          "default_value_repr": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "v_300ms",
          "type_desc": "positive int (samples)",
          "constraints": "= floor(0.3 * sampling_rate)",
          "required": true,
          "default_value_repr": ""
        }
      ],
      "status": "atomic",
      "children": [],
